FBIS4-28682 "dreas113_c_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-113 Daily Report 12 Jun 1994 North Korea `War Hysterics' Alleged `War Hysterics' Alleged SK1206090594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0814 GMT 12 Jun 94 SK1206090594 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN ["U.S. Imperialist Aggressors Stage Patriot Missile 'Operation Demonstration'" -- KCNA headline] [Text] Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The command of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces occupying South Korea opened to the public on Friday one battery of Patriot missiles at the Osan base in Kyonggi Province and staged an "operation demonstration", according to a radio report from Seoul. The U.S. military incited war fever against the North, declaring that "it is prepared to go into action any moment". It clearly shows what extent the war hysterics of the U.S. imperialist aggressors against the DPRK has gone that they are even displaying patriot missiles, bringing the situation to a dangerous phase over its fictitious "nuclear issue."
